title: Senate passes bill to avert government shutdown, sends to House
text:
Senate passes bill to avert governmen... Senate passes bill to avert government shutdown, sends to House There are 1 comment on the Yahoo! story from 11 hrs ago, titled Senate passes bill to avert government shutdown, sends to House . In it, Yahoo! reports that: 
The U.S. Senate on Wednesday overwhelmingly passed legislation to avert a government shutdown, sending the measure to the House of Representatives just hours before funding for federal agencies runs out at midnight. Passed by a 78-20 vote, the bill would keep federal agencies funded at current levels through Dec. 11. It does not include a controversial provision to cut off money to Planned Parenthood that many conservative Republicans had demanded. Join the discussion below, or Read more at Yahoo!.
